00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:58.560
An even better phrase though, would be "non-random
selection" or maybe even "non-random elimination."

00:02:58.560 --> 00:03:03.620
While all genetic mutations are generated
by a random copying error, or random variation

00:03:03.629 --> 00:03:08.750
completely beyond the animal's control, the
selection of those traits is not random. Successful

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:14.519
variations that allow you to survive and reproduce
are determined by the very specific circumstances

00:03:14.519 --> 00:03:19.379
of your environment, where elimination (death)
might not be far away.

00:03:19.379 --> 00:03:24.120
So, the selection of your traits is done by
a very specific, and sometimes brutal, list

00:03:24.120 --> 00:03:28.390
of criteria. This is why people who say that
they don't understand how all animals could

00:03:28.390 --> 00:03:32.250
have "evolved by chance" don't really understand
how evolution works.

